11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 587, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 587. The fee for such examinations shall be set by
15 rules promulgated by the Board of Examiners in Optometry, not to be
16 less than One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) and not to exceed Two
17 Hundred Dollars ($200.00), and a yearly license fee set by rules
18 promulgated by the Board of Examiners in Optometry, not to exceed
19 Three Hundred Dollars ($300.00) Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
20 shall be paid each fiscal year by all persons holding a license to
21 practice optometry in this state, and shall be paid not later than
22 the 30th day of June of each year. In the event of default of
23 payment of such license fee by any person, his or her certificate
24 shall be revoked by the Board of Examiners who shall take such
