1 acti on only after notifying the person in default by registered mail
2 and allowing that person fifteen (15) days in which to comply with
3 this requirement. The Board shall be paid travel expenses as
4 provided in the State Travel Reimbursement Act, Section 500.1 et
5 seq. of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes. The secretary-treasurer
6 shall receive compensation fixed by the Board, not to exceed Two
7 Hundred Dollars ($200.00) per month. All fees and charges collected
8 by the secretary-treasurer of the Board shall be paid on the first
9 day of each month into a revolving fund in the State Treasury to be
10 designated as the "Optometry Board Revolving Fund". This fund shall
11 consist of all monies received by the Board of Optometry other than
12 appropriated funds. The revolving fund shall be a continuing fund
13 not subject to fiscal year limitations and shall be under the
14 control and management of the Board of Optometry. Expenditures from
15 this fund shall be made pursuant to the purposes of Sections 581
16 through 606 of this title and without legislative approval.
17 Warrants for expenditures shall be drawn by the State Treasurer
18 based on claims signed by an authorized employee or employees of the
19 Board of Optometry and approved for payment by the Director of the
20 Office of Management and Enterprise Services.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
